                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful, regular, by a well-trained hand</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg> The hand is similar to that of <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda
                           Māryām</persName>.<date>Mid-18th cent. (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits or headings of the texts;
                           directives for the celebrants; abbreviations; the words (እሁነ፡) እገሌ፡ and
                           እገሊት፡ standing for the name of the deceased or the baptised; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD; &#xD; The text
                           on fol. 7r is written alternately in red and black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
